The paper proposes a new algorithm for solving optimization problems that extend Boolean Satisfiability (SAT), specifically Pseudo-Boolean Optimization (PBO) and Maximum Satisfiability (MaxSAT). These problems are commonly studied in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), logic in computer science (cs.LO), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper's focus on optimization and algorithm design suggests that it is likely to be classified under one or more of these sub-categories.
